# /sp.specify
## AI-Powered Content Generation & Optimization Tool — Project Specifications

---

## 1. User Requirements & Stories
- Users can input topic, audience, tone, style, format, and content length.
- Users can generate content, view SEO suggestions, and iteratively refine outputs.
- Users can export content for blogs, social media, ad campaigns, or marketing platforms.
- Users expect actionable feedback and readability improvement suggestions.

---

## 2. Content Generation Spec
- Generate high-quality first-pass content drafts.
- Inputs: topic, audience, tone, style, format, length.
- Output: coherent, relevant content draft.
- Constraints: preserve user intent; no SEO optimization at this stage.

---

## 3. SEO Optimization Spec
- Analyze content for keyword density, headings, meta description, and readability.
- Provide actionable, ethical SEO recommendations.
- Iterative feedback loop for content refinement.
- Input: content draft. Output: SEO improvement report.

---

## 4. Quality Review Spec
- Improve clarity, readability, engagement, and flow.
- Preserve tone and meaning of original content.
- Provide short summary of improvements.
- Input: content draft (with or without SEO suggestions). Output: polished content.

---

## 5. Plagiarism & Ethical Safeguard Spec
- Detect and flag plagiarism and duplicate content.
- Identify ethical risks or policy violations.
- Ensure compliance with copyright and professional guidelines.
- Input: content draft. Output: originality & ethics report.

---

## 6. Research Subagent Spec
- Gather relevant data, references, or examples to support content creation.
- Focused and goal-specific information retrieval.
- Input: search queries, target domains. Output: structured research results.

---

## 7. Web Platform & User Interface Spec
- Responsive and intuitive UI for content creation, SEO feedback, and quality review.
- Supports exportable outputs (blogs, social media posts, campaigns).
- Includes analytics dashboard to track content performance and refinement metrics.

---

## 8. Subagent & Workflow Spec
- Define subagents: Content Generation, SEO Optimization, Quality Review, Research, Orchestrator (optional).
- Inputs, outputs, and task scope strictly defined for each subagent.
- Follow one-task → one-completion execution model.
- Main system orchestrates subagent execution and integrates outputs.

---

## 9. Performance & Reliability Spec
- Target subagent response time: ≤10 seconds for content generation.
- High reliability and graceful error handling.
- Secure handling of API keys and user inputs.
- Mitigate risks: rate limiting for LLM APIs, content bias detection, search query refinement.

---

**All specifications must be followed for modular, scalable, and high-quality development of the AI content generation and optimization tool.**
